HAVANA , September 27 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The Cuban government has reinforced security measures on its borders to drug trafficking to and fro the island country , which is located on the drug traffic route from South America to the United States and Europe , a TV report said on Wednesday .
Nine out of every 10 persons detained in Cuban airports who are suspected of being drug traffickers carry cocaine in their stomachs , adhered to their body , or in their luggage , said the report .
According to official statistics , over 40 tons of drugs have been seized in the last six years , most of which was destined for the United States .
Also , more than 140 drug trafficking maritime or air operations have been interrupted .
Cuba has signed 25 agreements with countries in America , the Caribbean , and Europe , pledging to intensify its fight against drug trafficking .
